  <brief_title>DepoCyt Therapy in Patients With Neoplastic Meningitis From Lymphoma or a Solid Tumor</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Randomized Clinical Study to Determine the Patient Benefit and Safety of Depocyt (Cytarabine Liposome Injection) for the Treatment of Neoplastic Meningitis</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Pacira Pharmaceuticals, Inc</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Pacira Pharmaceuticals, Inc</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to find out how well an experimental drug called DepoCyt works
      for neoplastic meningitis (cancer that has spread to the tissues around the brain and spinal
      cord). DepoCyt is a new slow-release form of the cancer drug called ara-C (cytarabine).
      Cytarabine has been used for many years to treat cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
